  <title translate="true">XS1708</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">XS1708</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS1708</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Fixed size buffers can only be accessed through locals or fields</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">A new feature in X# 2.0 is the ability to define an in-line array inside of a struct. Such arrays can only be accessed via local variables or fields, and may not be referenced as intermediate values on the left-hand side of an expression. Also, the arrays cannot be accessed by fields that are static or readonly.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">To resolve this error, define an array variable, and assign the in-line array to the variable. Or, remove the static or readonly modifier from the field representing the in-line array.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following sample generates XS1708.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// XS1708.prg &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// compile with: /unsafe &#160;</text><br/></para>
  </body>
</topic>
